    <stitle>13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14613 - REMOVE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302752">Figure 52</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1302752" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302752" filename="../figg13/G1302752.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 52. Auxiliary Drive Gear Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut the lockwire and remove the bolts from the bearing retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302753">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302753" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302753" filename="../figg13/G1302753.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 53. Cut Lockwire and Remove Bolts From Bearing Retainer Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the mainshaft rear groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302754">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302754" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302754" filename="../figg13/G1302754.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 54. Remove Snap Ring From Mainshaft Rear Groove</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the splined washer from inside front auxiliary drive gear assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302755">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302755" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302755" filename="../figg13/G1302755.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 55. Remove Splined Washer From Inside Front Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove six bolts from the auxiliary bearing retainer ring. Insert three bolts in the
                specially tapped holes of the retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302756">Figure 56</hotlnk>). Tighten bolts evenly to pull the auxiliary drive gear
                assembly from the case bore.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302756" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302756" filename="../figg13/G1302756.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Insert Bolts in Retainer Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front auxiliary drive gear from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302757">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302757" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302757" filename="../figg13/G1302757.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 57. Remove Front Auxiliary Drive Gear From Mainshaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the splined washer from the mainshaft. Also remove the front auxiliary drive gear
                retaining snap ring from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302758">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302758" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302758" filename="../figg13/G1302758.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 58. Remove Front Auxiliary Drive Gear Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
